  <title>Mechanism-Synthesis</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Mechanism Synthesis<keyword>Dimensional Synthesis</keyword><keyword>Number Synthesis</keyword><keyword>Type Synthesis</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass=" " style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Mechanism Synthesis</text>: the application of geometry to find a mechanism that provides a design requirement. The requirements include: Position Synthesis, Function Generation, Coupler Point Synthesis. There are three stages Mechanism Synthesis: </para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Type Synthesis</text> (gives the type of mechanism: linkages, gears, cams, belts...)</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Number Synthesis</text> (gives the number of Parts, how many degrees-of-freedom)</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Dimensional Synthesis</text> (gives the exact lengths of Parts, the exact Cam-Profile)</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">Compare with <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Mechanism-Analysis">Mechanism Analysis</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
